20party%20could%20develop%20a%20structured%20leadership%20in%20state%20after%20state.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Rajasthan%2C%20it%20has%20amicably%20settled%2C%20at%20least%20until%20the%20elections%2C%20the%20dispute%20between%20Sachin%20Pilot%20and%20chief%20minister%20Ashok%20Gehlot.%20Pilot%E2%80%99s%20cooperation%20has%20improved%20the%20party%E2%80%99s%20chances%20in%20the%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20Chhatisgarh%2C%20T.S.%20Singh%20Deo%20was%20persuaded%20to%20accept%20the%20compromise%20to%20function%20as%20deputy%20chief%20minister.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3ESingh%20Deo%20was%20a%20claimant%20for%20the%20CM%E2%80%99s%20post%20and%20had%20refused%20to%20work%20under%20Bupesh%20Baghel.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ED.K.%20Shiv%20Kumar%2C%20who%20had%20fiercely%20fought%20for%20the%20chief%20ministership%20of%20Karnataka%2C%20finally%20agreed%20to%20function%20as%20deputy%20chief%20minister%20in%20the%20wider%20interest%20of%20the%20party.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20worst%20challenge%20is%20in%20Delhi%2C%20where%20the%20state%20Congress%20leaders%20are%20adamant%20against%20any%20compromise.%20Things%20are%20gradually%20changing%2C%20with%20the%20state%20leaders%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Fcities%2Fdelhi-news%2Feye-on-2024-polls-congress-targets-bjp-at-delhi-rally-101697394766033.html%5C%22%3Eshifting%20focus%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20fighting%20against%20the%20BJP.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ECompare%20such%20compromises%20with%20the%20high-handed%20way%20in%20which%20Amit%20Shah%20removed%20and%20appointed%20CMs%20in%20BJP-ruled%20states%20like%20Gujarat%20and%20Uttarakhand.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20latter%E2%80%99s%20case%20is%20more%20curious.%20There%20were%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Fopinion%2Feditorial%2Futtarakhand-4-months-3-chief-ministers-1004928.html%5C%22%3Ethree%20CMs%20in%20four%20months%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20mid-2021%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAnother%20healthy%20trend%20in%20the%20Congress%20has%20been%20the%20grooming%20of%20a%20leadership%20structure%20in%20states.%20The%20new%20policy%20is%20based%20on%20the%20assumption%20that%20elections%20are%20won%20on%20cooperative%20efforts%20by%20the%20central%20and%20state%20leaders.%20This%20is%20in%20sharp%20contrast%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20policy%20of%20treating%20state%20leaders%20as%20dispensable%20and%20seeking%20votes%20by%20leveraging%20his%20popularity.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ELike%20all%20good%20authoritarian%20leaders%2C%20his%20emphasis%20has%20been%20to%20directly%20reach%20out%20to%20the%20voters%20without%20anyone%20in%20between.%20This%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fcity%2Fahmedabad%2Fgujarat-new-cabinet-delayed-as-old-guard-weighs-on-fresh-start%2Farticleshow%2F86249775.cms%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20revolts%3C%2Fa%3E%20by%20the%20leaders%20who%20had%20devoted%20their%20entire%20lives%20to%20the%20BJP%20and%20were%20ignored.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20Read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdouble-engine-bjp-modi-shah%5C%22%3EThe%20%E2%80%98Double%20Engine%E2%80%99%20is%20Pass%C3%A9%2C%20Hereafter%20Modi-Shah%20Will%20Pick%20or%20Junk%20BJP%20CMs%20at%20Will%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EFrom%20dissent%20to%20consensus%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Congress%20suffered%20its%20worst%20desertions%20after%20the%202019%20elections%2C%20when%20its%20tally%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20was%20just%2052.%20Narendra%20Modi%20emerged%20as%20an%20uncrowned%20king.%20The%20party%20had%20to%20contend%20with%20large-scale%20defections%2C%20some%20to%20the%20BJP%2C%20others%20to%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20and%20Trinamool%20Congress.%20Incidentally%2C%20the%20BJP%20has%20been%20very%20selective%20in%20accommodating%20defectors%20from%20the%20Congress.%20Those%20were%20the%20days%20when%20the%20Congress%20was%20seen%20as%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.deccanherald.com%2Findia%2Flike-a-drowning-boat-in-turbulent-ocean-g23-leaders-on-congress-debacle-1090599.html%5C%22%3Esinking%20boat%20in%20a%20turbulent%20sea%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20August%202020%2C%20a%20group%20of%2023%20senior%20leaders%20in%20a%20letter%20to%20interim%20Congress%20president%20Indira%20Gandhi%20demanded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.news18.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Fgroup-of-23-the-congress-leaders-who-wrote-the-letter-of-dissent-why-they-are-important-2813123.html%5C%22%3Ewide-ranging%20reforms%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20included%20collective%20leadership%20and%20elections%20to%20choose%20the%20party%20president%20and%20all%20organisational%20committees.%20Among%20this%20%E2%80%98G-23%E2%80%99%20were%20senior%20leaders%20like%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20Anand%20Sharma%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%20and%20Manish%20Tiwari%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20phenomenon%20lasted%20for%20about%20two%20years%20while%20the%20Congress%20leadership%20remained%20adamant.%20In%20the%20process%2C%20many%20more%20members%20departed.%20Some%20like%20Jitin%20Prasada%20joined%20the%20BJP%2C%20Kapil%20Sibal%20became%20an%20independent%20leader%20and%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%20formed%20his%20own%20party.%20Initially%2C%20the%20leadership%20dismissed%20the%20G-23%20implosion%20as%20a%20revolt.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20the%20G-23%20also%20eventually%20triggered%20the%20transformation%20of%20the%20Indian%20National%20Congress%20as%20a%20vigorous%20movement.%20The%20process%2C%20in%20fact%2C%20had%20begun%20even%20before%20Kharge%E2%80%99s%20election%20as%20president%20and%20the%20appointment%20of%20Jairam%20Ramesh%20as%20AICC%E2%80%99s%20communication%20head.%20The%20G-23%20is%20now%20a%20thing%20of%20the%20past.%20Most%20of%20its%20prominent%20members%20have%20been%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fcongress-working-committee-reshuffle-shashi-tharoor-sachin-pilot-and-gaurav-gogoi-among-20-new-faces-inducted-101692556638462.html%5C%22%3Eaccommodated%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20the%20Congress%20Working%20Committee%20or%20other%20important%20positions.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBy%202022%2C%20regional%20parties%20like%20TMC%20and%20KCR%E2%80%99s%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%20had%20opened%20offices%20in%20Delhi.%20This%20was%20part%20of%20their%20prime%20ministerial%20ambitions.%20The%20Congress%20resurgence%20has%20made%20them%20retreat.%20Among%20the%20opposition%20parties%2C%20the%20Congress%20alone%20has%20the%20infrastructure%20to%20daily%20pound%20the%20ruling%20party%20on%20emerging%20issues%2C%20including%20the%20prime%20minister%E2%80%99s%20relationship%20with%20Gautam%20Adani.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20candidate%20list%20is%20finalised%20by%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20his%20technocrats%2C%20the%20Congress%20this%20time%20is%20experimenting%20with%20a%20new%20system%20to%20provide%20more%20power%20to%20state%20leaders.%20The%20selection%20of%20candidates%20was%20left%20to%20the%20state%20leaders.%20This%20time%2C%20the%20central%20election%20committee%20focused%20on%20trying%20for%20consensus%20on%20disputed%20names.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20new%20system%20has%20worked%20smoothly.%20There%20were%20a%20few%20protests%20by%20the%20disappointed%20aspirants%2C%20which%20is%20to%20be%20expected.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2019%2F12%2F11191048%2Fcongress-leaders.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2