67224568.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Simultaneous%20Polls%20Only%20Possible%20by%202029%2C%20Law%20Commission%20Tells%20Kovind%20Panel%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26110403%2FThe-Wire-56.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%20on%20Wednesday%2C%20October%2025%2C%20presented%20a%20roadmap%2C%20including%20possible%20changes%20required%20to%20the%20constitution%2C%C2%A0to%20the%20high-level%20panel%20headed%20by%20former%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%20looking%20into%20the%20proposal%20of%20simultaneous%20polls.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flaw-commission-presents-roadmap-on-one-nation-one-election-to-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel%2Farticle67459227.ece%5C%22%3EAccording%20to%3Cem%3E%20The%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20commission%20said%20the%20proposal%20can%20only%20be%20materialised%20by%20the%202029%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20as%20it%20would%2C%20over%20time%2C%20work%20out%20a%20formula%20to%20synchronise%20all%20assembly%20elections%2C%20either%20by%20extending%20or%20reducing%20the%20tenures%20of%20respective%20state%20assemblies.%20A%20report%20from%20the%20Law%20Commission%20is%20still%20pending%20in%20this%20regard%2C%20and%20it%20will%20be%20invited%20again%20for%20another%20round%20of%20discussions%20by%20the%20Kovind%20panel.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20Law%20Commission%20is%20looking%20into%20the%20proposal%20of%20holding%20assembly%20and%20parliament%20elections%20at%20once%2C%20the%20panel%20headed%20by%20the%20former%20president%20is%20exploring%20ways%20to%20synchronise%20assembly%2C%20parliament%2C%20municipality%2C%20and%20panchayat%20elections%20all%20at%20once.%20The%20Kovind%20Panel%20has%20been%20officially%20renamed%20as%20the%C2%A0High%20Level%20Committee%20(HLC)%20on%20One%20Nation%2C%20One%20Election%2C%20a%20Law%20Ministry%20release%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20HLC%20has%20already%20written%20to%20political%20parties%20across%20the%20country%20to%20elicit%20their%20views%20on%20the%20matter.%20Letters%20have%20so%20far%20been%20sent%20to%20six%20national%20parties%2C%2033%20state%20parties%2C%20and%20seven%20registered%20unrecognised%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EAt%20Wednesday%E2%80%99s%20meeting%2C%20the%20HLC%20took%20%E2%80%9Cnote%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20resignation%20of%20the%C2%A0resignation%20of%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Choudhury%2C%20leader%20of%20the%20single%20largest%20party%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20from%20membership%20of%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20meeting%20was%20attended%20by%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%2C%20former%20leader%20of%20the%20Opposition%20in%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%3B%20law%20minister%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%3B%20former%20chairman%20of%20the%2015th%20finance%20commission%20N.K.%20Singh%3B%20former%20Lok%20Sabha%20secretary%20general%20Subhash%20C.%20Kashyap%3B%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%3B%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20official%20notification%20issued%20on%20September%202%2C%20constituting%20the%20Kovind%20Panel%2C%20the%20government%20said%20holding%20frequent%20elections%20so%20far%20has%20resulted%20in%20massive%20expenditure%2C%20diversion%20of%20official%20machinery%20for%20election%20purposes%2C%20and%20disruption%20in%20developmental%20activity%20due%20to%20the%20Model%20Code%20of%20Conduct.%20Therefore%2C%20if%20simultaneous%20polls%20are%20held%2C%20the%20government%20notification%20said%2C%20all%20three%20of%20them%20can%20be%20tackled.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20there%20have%20been%20several%20criticisms%20against%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20proposal%20of%20one%20nation%2C%20one%20election.%20Writing%20in%20the%20%3Cem%3EIndian%20Express%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20former%20election%20commissioner%20Ashok%20Lavasa%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsimultaneous-polls-a-point-by-point-rebuttal-of-the-govts-reasoning-by-former-ec-ashok-lavasa%5C%22%3Ehad%20said%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20more%20meaningful%20and%20substantive%20electoral%20reforms%20that%20need%20the%20urgent%20attention%20of%20Parliament.%20There%20are%20far%20more%20effective%20ways%20to%20bring%20about%20greater%20transparency%20in%20election-related%20expenditure%20than%20chasing%20the%20mechanical%20scheduling%20of%20elections.%20Yes%2C%20there%20might%20be%20a%20need%20to%20bring%20about%20more%20managerial%20efficiency%20in%20conducting%20elections%20but%20that%20might%20not%20need%20onerous%20constitutional%20amendments.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3ELavasa%20then%20goes%20on%20to%20say%2C%20the%20reasons%20cited%20by%20the%20government%20in%20favour%20of%20its%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%2C%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20are%20nothing%20more%20than%20%E2%80%9Cinstinctive%20surmise(s)%20that%20cannot%20form%20a%20sufficient%20basis%20for%20taking%20a%20decision%20that%20has%20significant%20implications%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1698299410000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2F26110403%2FThe-Wire-56.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsimultaneous-polls-only-possible-by-2029-law-commission-tells-kovind-panel%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20Law%20Commission%20said%20the%20proposal%20can%20only%20be%20materialised%20by%20the%202029%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20as%20it%20would%2C%20over%20time%2C%20work%20out%20a%20formula%20to%20synchronise%20all%20assembly%20elections%2C%20either%20by%20extending%20or%20reducing%20the%20tenures%20of%20state%20assemblies.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A3%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsimultaneous-polls-only-possible-by-2029-law-commission-tells-kovind-panel%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%2