2%80%9CAnything%20remaining%20after%20the%20camp%20would%20be%20donated%20to%20NGOs%2C%E2%80%9D%20adds%20Mamatha.%20On%20Sundays%2C%20they%20would%20plan%20some%20special%20activity%2C%20like%20going%20on%20an%20excursion%20to%20nearby%20places%20or%20a%20bird-watching%20trip.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EThe%20camps%20that%20usually%20ran%20for%203-4%20weeks%20were%20based%20on%20a%20theme%20every%20year.%20This%20would%20be%20decided%20mostly%20by%20Sudha%20but%20in%20consultation%20with%20her%20team%20of%20teachers.%20%E2%80%9CInnovative%20ideas%20were%20welcomed%2C%20like%20the%20%3Cem%3EAata%20Oota%3C%2Fem%3E%20Camp%2C%20which%20involved%20making%20food%20without%20cooking.%20Also%2C%20each%20team%20would%20be%20named%20by%20a%20food%20item%20they%20did%20not%20like.%20This%20was%20done%20to%20foster%20a%20change%20of%20attitude%20towards%20the%20food%20item.%20After%20all%2C%20you%20cannot%20not%20like%20your%20team!%E2%80%9D%20notes%20Srimathi.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cp%3EShe%20had%20come%20to%20enrol%20her%20son%20for%20the%20camp%20but%20felt%20drawn%20to%20assist%20a%20child%20with%20disabilities%20in%20the%20camp.%20Observing%20her%20patience%20and%20how%20the%20child%20obeyed%20her%2C%20Sudha%20took%20it%20upon%20herself%20to%20talk%20to%20Srimathi%E2%80%99s%20husband.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20asked%20him%20to%20get%20me%20admitted%20into%20some%20course%20and%20not%20let%20my%20talent%20go%20to%20waste.%20I%20went%20on%20to%20do%20a%20Montessori%20course%20and%20now%20I%20run%20my%20own%20school.%20I%20have%20her%20picture%20alongside%20that%20of%20God%20in%20my%20house%20and%20I%20bow%20to%20both.%20She%20is%20my%20living%20God%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20explaining%20how%20this%20turned%20her%20life%20around.%3C%2Fp%3E%20%3Cfigure%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20960px)%20100vw%2C%20960px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F10%2FIMG-20230928-WA0008_11zon-1698072880.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5